article.headline: North Texas 85, Cameron 47
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Kendrick Davis scored 19 points and Michael Sturns added 18 to lead North Texas to an 85-47 win over Cameron on Friday night in the season opener for both teams. North Texas led 40-26 at the half and shot 45 percent from the field. Also scoring in the double digits for North Texas was Calvin Watson with 10. David shot 7-of-10 from the field, and Sturns shot 7-of-11. Harold Stewart had 11 rebounds to lead the Mean Green. Matthew Reid led Cameron with 16 points. Greg Mercer had six rebounds.
